subSubSection.paragraph:
Since 1899, the species-group name 

Inachus bifidus
Marion de Procé, 1822

, has not been used as a valid name for the taxon it denotes, which fulfils Article 23.9.1.1 of the Code. In the past 44 years, 30 publications by 45 different authors have used the name 

Mithrax asper
H. 
Milne Edwards, 1831

, as the valid name for the taxon it denotes (viz., 
Takeda, 1973: 109
; Griffin, 1974: 28; 
Griffin & Tranter, 1974: 181
, 182; 
Lundoer, 1974: 5
(list); 
Sakai, 1976: 246
, pl. 89 fig. 3; 
Serène et al., 1976: 16
(list); 
